'''Kingsbridge Wind Power Project''', also referred to as '''Kingsbridge 1 Wind facility ''', refers to a large [[wind farm]] owned and operated by Capital Power Corporation.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.sedar.com/GetFile.do?lang=EN&docClass=1&issuerNo=00028458&fileName=/csfsprod/data127/filings/01871414/00000001/i%3A%5CSEDAR%5CCapitalPowerCorporation%5CDEC2011Annuals%5CCPCFinal2011AIF.pdf|work=2011 Annual Information Form, Capital Power|publisher=System for Electronic Document Analysis and Retrieveal (SEDAR)|accessdate=June 1, 2012|title=2011 Annual Information Form, Capital Power}}</ref> Kingsbridge 1 Wind facility is located between [[Goderich, Ontario|Goderich]] and [[Kincardine, Ontario]]. The Kingsbridge 1 Wind facility is located on the southeast shore of [[Lake Huron]] in the township of [[Ashfield-Colborne-Wawanosh]] and consists of 22 1.8 [[Megawatt|MW]] [[Vestas]] V80 [[wind turbines]] with a capacity of 39.6 MW.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.epcor.ca/SiteCollectionDocuments/Communities/Ontario/pdf/Kingsbridgefactsheet.pdf | title=Kingsbridge Fact Sheet, EPCOR }}{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Each tower is over 78 meters tall and weigh around 195 metric tonnes.<ref>[http://www.epcor.ca/SiteCollectionDocuments/Environment/pdfs/KingsbridgeWindPowerProject.pdf Kingsbridge Wind Power Project]{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The project consists of two phases and currently provides power to on average 12,500 homes.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.epcor.ca/SiteCollectionDocuments/Environment/pdfs/KingsbridgeWindPowerProject.pdf | title=Kingsbridge Fact Sheet Two, EPCOR }}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
In 2004, the first phase was awarded a generation contract by the Government of [[Ontario]] as part of its renewable energy [[RFP]]. Construction has since been completed and the project is fully operational.
In 2005, the second phase received a generation contract from the provincial government.
