{{Infobox dam | name = Lai Châu Dam | image = Thuy dien Lai Chau.jpg | image_size = 235px | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Vietnam | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|22|8|22|N|102|59|7|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = [[Vietnam]] | location = [[Lai Châu Province]] | status = O | construction_began = 2011 | opening = 20 December 2016 | demolished = | cost = [[Vietnamese đồng|VND]] 35,700 billion | owner = [[Vietnam Electricity|EVN]] | dam_type = | dam_length = | dam_height = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | dam_crosses = [[Da River]] | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = | res_capacity_total = | res_catchment = | res_surface = | res_max_depth = | res_tidal_range = | plant_operator = [[Vietnam Electricity|EVN]] | plant_commission = 2017 (expected) | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = 3 x 400&nbsp;MW [[Francis turbine]]s<!-- -->{{Infobox power station |name = Lai Châu Dam |embed = yes | ps_electrical_capacity= 1,200&nbsp;MW (max. planned) | ps_electrical_cap_fac= 45% | ps_annual_generation= 4,670&nbsp;GWh/yr }} | website = | extra = }} The '''Lai Châu Dam''' is a hydroelectric dam on the [[Black River (Asia)|Black River]] inaugurated on 20 December 2016 in [[Nậm Nhùn District]], [[Lai Chau Province]], [[Vietnam]]. The owner of the power station is [[Vietnam Electricity]].<ref name="evn.com.vn">{{cite news | url = http://en.evn.com.vn/d6/news/Inauguration-of-Lai-Chau-hydropower-project-0-142-342.aspx | title = Inauguration of Lai Chau hydropower project | agency = [[Vietnam Electricity|EVN]] | work = EVNICT | date = | accessdate = 2018-05-04}} </ref>
Dam was designed by [[Hydroproject]], a [[Russia]]n hydrotechnical design firm,<ref name="rushydro"> {{cite press release | script-title=ru:Закончена разработка технического проекта гидроузла Лай Чау во Вьетнаме | publisher= [[RusHydro]] | date = 2012-06-01 | url= http://www.rushydro.ru/press/holding-news/79124.html | accessdate = 2013-12-23 | language= Russian}} </ref> in collaboration with the Vietnamese company Power Construction No.1 JSC.<ref name="evn.com.vn"/> The ground clearance works and relocation of people was completed by September 2010.<ref name=intellasia071010> {{cite news | url = http://www.intellasia.net/news/articles/infra_resources/111305603.shtml | title = First phase of Lai Chau hydropower plant completed | agency = Intellasia News Services | work = Kinh Te Vietnam & The Gioi | date = 2010-10-07 | accessdate = 2011-01-22}} </ref> Construction started on 5 January 2011; it was expected to be operational by 2017 with the first turbine put into operation in 2016,<ref name=intellasia201210> {{cite news | url = http://www.intellasia.net/news/articles/infra_resources/111311728.shtml | title = Construction on Lai Chau hydropower plant to be started | agency = Intellasia News Services | work = Kinh Te Vietnam & The Gioi | date = 2010-12-20 | accessdate = 2011-01-22}} </ref><ref name=intellasia050111/> but the plant was inaugurated on 20 December 2016, one year ahead of the schedule, in a ceremony attended by the Deputy Prime Minister [[Trịnh Đình Dũng]] and other important personalities.<ref name="evn.com.vn"/>
The power station has three [[Francis turbine]]s with a capacity of 400&nbsp;MW each. Turbines have been manufactured at the [[Alstom]]'s plant in [[Tianjin]], [[China]].<ref name=pe150113> {{cite news | url = http://www.power-eng.com/news/2013/01/15/alstom-hydrochina-secure-major-vietnam-hydro-power-deal.html | title = Alstom, Hydrochina secure major Vietnam hydro power deal | work = [[Power Engineering (magazine)|Power Engineering]] | publisher = [[PennWell Corporation]] | date = 2013-01-15 | accessdate = 2013-01-15}} </ref><ref name=intellasia150113> {{cite news |url = http://www.intellasia.net/alstom-to-make-equipment-for-lai-chau-hydropower-plant-258793 |title = Alstom to make equipment for Lai Chau hydropower plant |agency = Intellasia News Services |work = [[Saigon Times Daily]] |date = 2013-01-15 |accessdate = 2013-01-15 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140303083624/http://www.intellasia.net/alstom-to-make-equipment-for-lai-chau-hydropower-plant-258793 |archivedate = 2014-03-03 |df = }} </ref> The total capacity of the station is 1,200&nbsp;MW. It is the third largest hydroelectric power station in Vietnam<ref name=intellasia201210/><ref name=intellasia050111> {{cite news |url=http://www.intellasia.net/news/articles/infra_resources/111313560.shtml |title=Work on Vietnam's third largest hydropower plant begins |agency=Intellasia News Services |work=Thanh Nien |date=2011-01-14 |accessdate=2011-01-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723160042/http://www.intellasia.net/news/articles/infra_resources/111313560.shtml |archivedate=2011-07-23 |df= }}</ref><ref name=pe150113/> and the third on the [[Da river]]. It is connected with the [[Hòa Bình Dam]] completed in 1994, and the [[Sơn La Dam]], inaugurated in 2012. The Lai Chau hydropower projects costed [[Vietnamese đồng|VND]] 35,700 billion.<ref name="evn.com.vn"/>
