{{Infobox power station | name = Langvann Power Station | name_official = ''Langvann kraftverk'' | image = Langvatn kraftverk Gildeskål.jpg | location_map = Nordland | location_map_caption = Location in [[Nordland]] county | coordinates = {{coord|66|53|16|N|14|08|55|E|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | location = [[Gildeskål]], [[Nordland]] | country = Norway | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = {{Start date and age|1979}} | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = [[Salten Kraftsamband]] | operator = | psps_upper_res = Fellvatnet | psps_upper_res_capacity= | psps_penstocks = | psps_lower_res = Langvatnet (Gildeskål) | psps_lower_res_capacity= | psps_hydraulic_head = 64&nbsp;m | psps_generators = 1 × 5&nbsp;MW | psps_pumpgenerators = | psps_pumps = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_electrical_capacity = 5 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = 11.5%<!-- 21,000 MWh/year / ( 5 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.115 --> | ps_annual_generation = 21 | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }} The '''Langvann Hydroelectric Power Station''' ({{lang-no|Langvann kraftverk}} or ''Langvann kraftstasjon'')<ref name="Sks">[https://www.sks.no/produksjon/kraftstasjoner/langvann/ SKS produksjon: Langvann.] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170202053647/https://www.sks.no/produksjon/kraftstasjoner/langvann/ |date=2017-02-02 }}</ref> is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] in the municipality of [[Gildeskål]] in [[Nordland]] [[Counties of Norway|county]], [[Norway]].<ref name="NVE">[http://publikasjoner.nve.no/publikasjonV/publikasjonV_32.pdf Norges Vassdrags- og Energiverk (NVE). 2016. ''Utbygd vannkraft i Norge pr. 01.01.1990.'' Oslo, p. 42.]</ref> It is sometimes referred to as the ''Langvatn kraftverk'',<ref name="NVE"/> which should not be confused with the [[Langvatn Hydroelectric Power Station]] in [[Rana, Norway|Rana]].
The plant utilizes a drop of {{convert|64|m|sp=us}}<ref name="Sks"/> between two lakes: ''[[Fellvatnet]]'' ({{lang-smj|Roavggojávrre}}),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yr.no/place/Norway/Nordland/Gildesk%C3%A5l/Fellvatnet/|title=Fellvatnet, Gildeskål (Nordland)|publisher=[[yr.no]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=January 29, 2017}}</ref> regulated between an elevation of {{cvt|393|m}} and {{cvt|333|m}}, and ''[[Langvatnet (Gildeskål)|Langvatnet]]'' ({{lang-smj|Gåddumjávrre}}),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.yr.no/place/Norway/Nordland/Gildesk%C3%A5l/Langvatnet/|title=Langvatnet, Gildeskål (Nordland)|publisher=[[yr.no]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=January 29, 2017}}</ref> regulated between an elevation of {{cvt|331|m}} and {{cvt|299|m}}.
The plant has a 5&nbsp;MW turbine and an average annual production of about 21&nbsp;GWh.<ref name="Sks"/> Its catchment area is {{convert|93|km2|sp=us}}.<ref name="Sks"/> The plant is owned by [[Salten Kraftsamband]] and it came into operation in 1979.<ref name="Sks"/> The plant is built into the mountainside at the end of a drain tunnel and the water it discharges is later used by the [[Sundsfjord Hydroelectric Power Station]].
